Locator/ID Separation Protocol (LISP)
Data-Plane Confidentiality
2017", shape=ellipse, URL="RFC8061.html", target="_top", tooltip="This document describes a mechanism for encrypting traffic encapsulated using the Locator/ID Separation Protocol (LISP).  The design describes how key exchange is achieved using existing LISP control-plane mechanisms as well as how to secure the LISP data plane from third-party surveillance attacks."];
